00:25:47,660 --> 00:25:50,100
 What's Isaiah saying?

582
00:25:50,100 --> 00:25:52,480
 God's gonna do all these great things.

583
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,480
 He's gonna come and he's gonna fight for his people.

584
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:56,340
 Hurrah, there's hope there.

585
00:25:56,340 --> 00:25:58,560
 He's gonna be a warrior.

586
00:25:58,560 --> 00:26:00,760
 He's gonna rescue us.

587
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:03,640
 But that hope and the boldness and the peace

588
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:07,340
 that it brings to our reality is only ours.

589
00:26:07,340 --> 00:26:09,560
 It can only be felt and transform us

590
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:11,360
 like a new song is meant to do

591
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:16,280
 if we put our faith in him.

592
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:18,740
 If our trust is in him,

593
00:26:18,740 --> 00:26:20,860
 which means that worship must include

594
00:26:20,860 --> 00:26:22,540
 what we do with our faith,

595
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:25,940
 not just what we say with our words.

596
00:26:25,940 --> 00:26:28,520
 True worship is not just about singing.

597
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,340
 True worship is about surrender.

598
00:26:30,340 --> 00:26:33,940
 True worship includes where you put your faith.

599
00:26:33,940 --> 00:26:36,220
 And the temptation when sin is blocking us,

600
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:37,440
 when things are difficult,

601
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:40,020
 is to sing of a new song

602
00:26:40,020 --> 00:26:42,460
 and sing of all the hope that God has for us

