00:27:53,420 --> 00:27:54,720
 you can't build your hope on that.

631
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:56,480
 Whatever you think you need to reach

632
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:59,240
 to reach financial stability,

633
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:00,720
 you can't build your hope on that.

634
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:03,920
 A specific political climate,

635
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:05,480
 you can't build your hope on that.

636
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:06,320
 You know why?

637
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:09,640
 Because those things were never meant to be

638
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,880
 where our hope and our trust is built.

639
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:16,520
 But Christ alone, the words we say in Christ alone,

640
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:20,280
 my hope, my strength, that's where our hope is.

641
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:23,680
 When we worship completely, yes, we say the words,

642
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:25,920
 but then we place our trust in him

643
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:29,640
 because only he can satisfy, only he can deliver.

644
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:35,560
 No lesser God can do what only God can do.

645
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:39,160
 So to worship is to put ourselves back in his hands

646
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:42,400
 and it's to do it daily, to do it regularly.

647
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:44,000
 It's not a one-time thing.

648
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:48,700
 Perhaps the most famous passage in the Bible about worship

649
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:52,000
 from most worship pastors comes from Romans 12.

650
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:54,720
 It says this, "Therefore, I urge you, brothers and sisters,

651
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:56,920
 "in view of God's mercy,

652
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,320
 "in light of what you've seen of him,

653
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:01,200
 "offer your bodies as a living sacrifice."

654
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:03,480
 Key word here, living.

655
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,480
 Doesn't mean that you do it one time and it's over.

656
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:07,080
 Living things has to repeat,

657
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:10,560
 it has to be something you do over and over and over again.

658
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:14,360
 True and proper worship, according to this passage by Paul,

659
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:18,480
 includes the consistent offering of yourselves,

660
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:20,040
 of ourselves to God.

661
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:22,320
 It's not something we do once.

662
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:27,320
 It's a living sacrifice, much like he is our living hope.

663
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:31,960
 It's to offer ourselves to God today and tomorrow.

664
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:35,200
 Every day that we have breath must be how,

665
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:37,560
 a day for us to engage in this kind of worship.

